# SplitBae — Architecture & Discipline

## Product goal
High-performance, platform-adaptive bill splitting (“Splid + Splitty”). **Lean APK/IPA**, **offline-first**, **sync-ready** without baking in a heavy on-device AI model.

---

## Git & delivery (trunk-based)
- **Repository**: Single private remote (e.g. GitHub)—**the box** where all history lives.
- **Commits**: Small, vertical slices (“Added IDR formatting”, “Wire backup export”). Each commit is a **snapshot** you can revert to if something breaks later.
- **Trunk**: `main` (or `trunk`) stays releasable; integrate via short-lived branches or direct commits—**no long-lived feature branches** that drift for weeks.
- **Issues**: **GitHub Issues** = task list. Prefer **one issue per small feature** (e.g. *#1 Setup Rust core*, *#2 Scan screen shell*) so work stays traceable and reviewable.

---

## Engineering principles
- **Modular**: Features are isolated; **core** is dependency-free of product fluff. Prefer many small files over “god” widgets.
- **Lean & fast**: No bundled LLM for OCR. Hot paths: **Rust** (math, settlement, merge rules) + **Flutter** (UI, I/O, platform APIs). Avoid redundant rebuilds; profile before micro-optimizing.
- **Professional**: Code should read like a maintained product—clear names, minimal noise, no filler comments. Prefer explicit types at boundaries (FRB, storage, exports).
- **Best tool for the job**: Rust for deterministic money and graph logic; Flutter for rendering and OS integration; native stacks for OCR (below); SQLite for structured local state; CRDT layer when sync ships—not before MVP storage is solid.

---

## Repository layout (target; grow into this as features land)

### Flutter (`lib/`)
- `core/` — theme tokens, routing shells, shared extensions, **no feature imports**.
- `features/<name>/` — `presentation/`, `application/` (providers), optional `data/` if feature-local only.
- `l10n/` — `.arb` sources + generated `app_localizations*.dart` (crowdsourced translations via GitHub PRs to ARB files).
- Platform-specific OCR lives behind a **single interface** (e.g. `ReceiptOcrPort`) with `android/` (ML Kit) and `ios/` (Vision) implementations—**not** duplicated parsing logic in Dart.

### Rust (`rust/src/`)
- `api/` — FRB-facing surface (`#[frb]` types and functions); keep thin.
- `domain/` — money types, ledger invariants (pure, unit-testable).
- `ledger/` (or `settlement/`) — split math, debt optimization, later CRDT merge **helpers** (actual sync transport stays in Flutter/Dart or a small native plugin—pick per evaluation).
- Avoid a single monolithic `simple.rs` long-term; split when the second major feature lands.

---

## Offline-first, backup, sync (roadmap)
| Layer | MVP (“Perfect Local Utility”) | Later |
|-------|-------------------------------|--------|
| Storage | **Encrypted SQLite** (e.g. SQLCipher or equivalent)—accept ~5–15% overhead for small rows; encrypt PII and payment handles. | Same DB + optional unencrypted export if user opts in. |
| Backup | **Manual backup**: export encrypted **`.sb_backup`** (or agreed extension); user saves to **iCloud / Google Drive / email**—no custom cloud backend in MVP. **Import** restores on-device. | Scheduled backups, optional unencrypted export. |
| Sync / Nextcloud | **Deferred.** No Nextcloud/WebDAV implementation in MVP; design storage paths so a future sync layer can attach. | **Nextcloud** / **iCloud** folder layout, **CRDT** merge (**Automerge** / **Yrs**), deterministic rules. |

**Rule**: Persistence and network are **Flutter + SQLite + platform channels**; Rust consumes **snapshots** or **commands** from Dart for heavy math, not raw socket I/O in MVP.

---

## Scanning & “direct-to-edit” (no heavy AI in binary)
- **Android**: **Google ML Kit** (Text Recognition)—on-device, small footprint, uses OEM/NPU where available.
- **iOS**: **Vision** (`VNRecognizeTextRequest`)—same rationale.
- **Flow**: Shutter → **live editable chips** (scan-to-live), not a static preview screen. Parsing into line items is **heuristic + user correction**; Rust stores **canonical** numbers after confirm.
- **Do not** ship a bundled transformer/LLM in the app for MVP OCR; optional server-side assist is a **later** product decision.

---

## Money & multi-currency model
- Persist **`CurrencyAmount`**: **numeric value + ISO 4217 code** (and scale policy explicit per type: minor units vs decimal—document in Rust). Adding FX later must **not** require a destructive migration—only new tables or nullable FX fields.
- FRB types should mirror this shape; avoid “naked” `f64` without currency in persisted models.

---

## Collaboration (post-MVP sync)
- **CRDTs** for same-ledger concurrent edits offline; merge must be **deterministic** across devices.
- Evaluate **Automerge-rs** / **Yrs** with a thin Dart bridge vs WASM—**decision recorded in repo** when sync starts; don’t block MVP on CRDT.

---

## UI: navigation, motion, wrappers
- **Dual wrappers** (Material 3 Expressive vs Liquid Glass)—semantic model once, presentation twice; see prior sections in git history if trimmed here.
- **Fluid bottom bar** (morphing center **+**, soft labels for Trips / Balances, horizontal carousels)—implement when shell exists; don’t premature-abstract before second tab.
- **Rive** for hero motion where it beats hand-rolled curves—keep asset count small; **120fps** is a target on ProMotion devices, not a guarantee on all hardware.

---

## Localization
- **Template**: `lib/l10n/app_en.arb` — add every new string here first; use **`@key` `description`** metadata for translator/MT context (screen, role of string, do-not-translate terms).
- **Other locales**: `app_<code>.arb` — values only; optional **Weblate/Crowdin/Tolgee** + ARB for crowdsourcing; **MT** (DeepL/Google/etc.) as draft → **human review** before merge.
- **Gaps**: `flutter gen-l10n` writes **`l10n_untranslated.txt`** (missing keys in non-English ARBs).
- Runtime: device default with in-app override (settings).

---

## Security & privacy
- SQLCipher (or platform-accepted equivalent) for **at-rest** encryption of the local DB.
- Backups: **encrypted** by default; clear UX for passphrase / OS keychain.

---

## MVP — “Perfect Local Utility” (revised)
Goal: ship a **flawless offline tool** first. **Nextcloud / multi-device sync** is explicitly **not** in MVP.

| MVP pillar | What ships |
|------------|------------|
| **Encrypted local DB** | At-rest encryption so data is safe if the device is lost/stolen (SQLCipher-class stack). |
| **“Snap & Split”** | **Native OCR** only (ML Kit on Android, Vision on iOS)—no bundled LLM. Bill → parsed lines → **assign items** to people; Rust holds canonical math. |
| **Manual backup** | One action exports an **encrypted `.sb_backup`** file; user stores it in **Drive / iCloud / email**. Matching **import** on another install. |
| **Native styles (proof)** | At least **one** screen that reads **Liquid Glass** on iOS and **one** that reads **Material 3 Expressive** on Android—same semantics, dual wrappers—so the design system is proven before the full shell. |

**Also in scope when capacity allows (same MVP spirit):** IDR-first flows, basic trip/group ledger, debt list + **Optimize** in Rust—**after** DB + backup + scan path are credible.

**Out of MVP**: Nextcloud/WebDAV sync, CRDT, FX, LLM inside the app, Rive-heavy navigation shell (optional stretch).

---

## Feature backlog (post-MVP)
Recurring expenses, auto-categories (server or light rules), advanced splits (shares / % / fixed), full multi-currency + FX, debt optimizer refinements, “who pays next?” scoreboard polish, PDF/WhatsApp flows, **user-chosen sync providers** (Nextcloud, iCloud paths).

---

## Cursor / AI usage
Prefer edits that **match existing style**. No drive-by renames. No essay comments. When adding files, place them under the **layout above** unless a one-off script in `tool/`.

